UNDIAGNOSED FATAL ILLNESS - PAKISTAN: (PUNJAB) MENINGITIS OR MENINGOENCEPHALITIS SUSPECTED, REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
*******************************************************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Fri 6 Jan 2023
Source: Tribune [edited]
https://tribune.com.pk/story/2394431/meningitis-outbreak-reported-in-ry-khan


District Health Authority CEO Dr Hassan Khan has said that 12 deaths, including 6 children, from meningitis within the same community, were reported in the Mouza Tajpur Pirwala of Rukanpur area earlier this week. The victims were aged between 2 years to 30 years. He added that when the deaths came to the notice of the health department, emergency response teams immediately reached the spot. On the instructions of the Deputy Commissioner, CEO Health, led these teams and all necessary measures were taken concerning public health.

Principal Sheikh Zaid Medical College formed a team consisting of three specialist doctors who diagnosed the disease as meningitis, in the light of the reported symptoms and laboratory reports. The DC held a detailed meeting with officers from Sheikh Zaid Medical College and the District Health Authority, where detailed instructions were issued regarding the future steps. Health Department teams reached the area and are taking the necessary steps on a daily basis.

On 5 Jan 2023, a team of specialist doctors from Sheikh Zaid Medical College and District Health Authority will return to the site and take blood samples and examine the residents there. The DC instructed that over the next 2 weeks, health department and finance department teams will be present in the affected area daily to prevent the further spread of meningitis.

[Byline: Farooq Sindhu]

